    <li><strong>Last new antibiotic class approved:</strong> 1987 — nearly 40 years ago</li>
    <li><strong>Clinical pipeline (2025):</strong> 90 agents total; only 15 innovative; only 5 effective against critical-priority pathogens (WHO, 2025)</li>
    <li><strong>Pipeline trend:</strong> Shrank from 97 agents in 2023 to 90 in 2025 (WHO, 2025)</li>
    <li><strong>VC investment in antibiotics:</strong> ~US$1.8B of US$38B total pharma R&D — under 5% (<em>npj Antimicrobials and Resistance</em>, 2025)</li>
    <li><strong>Preclinical research concentration:</strong> 90% conducted by firms with fewer than 50 employees (WHO, 2025)</li>
